text: Countess of Nottingham is the title given to the wife of the Earl of Nottingham. Women who have held the title include: *Catherine Carey, Countess of Nottingham (c.1547-1603) *Margaret Howard, Countess of Nottingham (c.1591-1639) *Essex Finch, Countess of Nottingham (c.1652-1684) *Anne Finch, Countess of Nottingham (1668–1743) *Georgiana Finch-Hatton, Countess of Winchilsea & Nottingham (1791-1835) #
title: Countess of Nottingham
